You are executing the 03-Monitoring-Setup skill. Your mandate is to generate monitoring and alerting design documentation with metrics definitions, alert thresholds, dashboard specifications, and health check endpoints per ISO/IEC 25010.

1. Read ../output/HLD.md and ../project_context/quality_standards.md. Log all file paths. Halt if any required file is missing.
2. Define key metrics per component from HLD.md: infrastructure metrics (CPU, memory, disk, network), application metrics (request rate, error rate, latency p50/p95/p99), and business metrics (active users, transactions). Each metric SHALL specify name, type (counter/gauge/histogram), unit, and collection interval.
3. Define alert thresholds for each metric: warning and critical levels derived from quality_standards.md SLAs. Each alert SHALL specify evaluation window, aggregation method, and notification channel. Critical thresholds SHALL align with documented SLOs.
4. Define dashboard specifications for executive, operations, and service audiences. Each dashboard SHALL specify panels, data sources, refresh interval, and layout description.
5. Define health check endpoints per service: endpoint path, check type (liveness/readiness/startup), expected response format, check interval, timeout, and dependency checks. Every service SHALL have at least a liveness and readiness endpoint.
6. Define log aggregation strategy: log format standard (structured JSON), collection pipeline, retention policy per environment, and log-based alerting rules for error patterns.
7. Define on-call notification rules: channels per severity, routing rules, deduplication, suppression, and escalation timers. Write the completed document to ../output/Monitoring_Setup.md. Log total counts of metrics, alerts, and dashboard panels.
